definition: to top up/to fill to the brim
abbr. for Canada 加拿大[Jia1 na2 da4]/surname Jia

to add/plus/(used after an adverb such as 不, 大, 稍 etc, and before a disyllabic verb, to indicate that the action of the verb is applied to sth or sb previously mentioned)/to apply (restrictions etc) to (sb)/to give (support, consideration etc) to (sth)

sentences.english: You drive to a gasoline station once a week, on average, and you fill up.
sentences.chinese: 你平均一周去一次加油站加满油。

sentences.english: I fill up the tank with gasoline about once a week.
sentences.chinese: 大约每个星期我加满一箱汽油。

sentences.english: He fille up the car with petrol.
In a tactical reload, you are "topping off" your gun with a fresh magazine.
sentences.chinese: 在战术换弹匣，你是用新的弹匣加满你的枪。

sentences.english: If you are using a concentrate, top up with filtered water to 23 liters.
sentences.chinese: 如果您使用集中，用被过滤的水加满对23公升。

sentences.english: Top up weekly with Lubrication Engineers 4090-H1 Quinplex food-grade grease.
sentences.chinese: 每周须给此系统加满食品级润滑脂。

sentences.english: NO. 005 BF replenisher tank is empty, add replenisher.
sentences.chinese: 漂白补充桶已空，请加满补充液。

sentences.english: Then a waiting man comes over, he wants to fill up for me.
sentences.chinese: 接着我名男服务员走过来，他想为我加满水。

sentences.english: NO. 004 CD replenisher tank is empty, add replenisher.
sentences.chinese: 显影补充桶已空，请加满补充液。

sentences.english: Keep a water bottle at your desk when you work, and refill it regularly.
sentences.chinese: 当你工作的时候，桌子上放一个水壶，定时的加满它。

sentences.english: The boy told the broom to fill a tub in the castle. The tub was empty.
sentences.chinese: 小伙子要扫帚把城堡里一个空浴缸的水加满。

sentences.english: A free gift is given with each fill-up.
sentences.chinese: 每加满一次油都可拿到免费赠品。

sentences.english: Please. Refill it for me just this once.
sentences.chinese: 但是我还需要，拜托，帮我加满这次就好。

sentences.english: I must get the car filled up at a gas station.
sentences.chinese: 我必须到加油站给车加满油。

sentences.english: A jigger of cognac, and you're going to top it off with champagne or sparkling wine.
sentences.chinese: 一量杯柯纳克白兰地，然后用香槟或汽水酒加满。

sentences.english: We tanked up at the filling station.
sentences.chinese: 我们在加油站给汽车加满了油。

definition: oil/fat/grease/petroleum/to apply tung oil, paint or varnish/oily/greasy/glib/cunning
to make up for what is lacking/to fill (a vacancy)/to replenish
to empty (a bag)/to turn inside out/to turn out
to start/to set in motion/to move/to march/to dig in (eating)/to tuck in (eating)
